Insteon Hub, Works with Alexa, the Google Assistant, & More, Create...
{"Author": "Kevin L", "Date": "on August 30, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Died after less than two years", "Text": "I have had two Insteon hubs died on me between one to two years of use. Perfect timing when the warranty just expired. What electronic devices that last less than two years now a day. There's definitely flaw in the circuit design that makes this device died prematurely. I used a UPS with surge protection so there shouldn't be a power surge that killed it. A pain was that I had to create new account and recreate the whole scenes and add all my Insteon devices all over again. Worse yet I need to use a different email account every time I set up a new hub. Stay away from this Insteon hub."}
{"Author": "SHAWN B. SMITH", "Date": "on August 25, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "CAVEAT EMPTOR - Very Disappointed", "Text": "Only using the Insteon app to interface with the Hub to control my devices. The app is glitchy and poorly designed. Customer support does not seem to be very knowledgeable on the product. I have spent two months working with customer support trying to work out scheduling issues to no avail. Have finally requested replacement of the Hub. Hopefully a new Hub will resolve the problem. If not, I have wasted a ton of money on Insteon devices that I can no longer adequately control in any automated manner. I cannot in good conscience recommend this product or any other Insteon product until they step up their game in product quality and customer support.\n\nNote: This is my second hub. The first died after three years!"}
{"Author": "Tobias Karlsson", "Date": "on August 20, 2018", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Disappointing", "Text": "This product could have so much to offer, but instead falls short in so many aspects:\n\n- Installation and getting up and running is pretty smooth and quick, so this is good.\n- The Android application seems to frequently get into a state where it acts up and the way to reset it is to go into settings and select 'Get Latest Configuration'.\n- The general application interface is clunky and slow.\n- The WEB interface basically does not work at all. I can't do anything useful there.\n- There is no documented direct-access to the device to automate things from, for example, a Raspberry Pi.\n\nOne might wonder, did they fire all their engineers after the first Proof-of-Concept."}
{"Author": "Skubidew", "Date": "on August 20, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Alexa integration, Stringify integration", "Text": "Works with insteon devices and Alexa will let you group with other vendors home automation products - excellent. Also set up complex scenes with Strigify. A word of caution though, if your hub goes bad, this will not drop in its place. You will have to setup all your devices again. Before ordering to replace a bad unit, contact smarthome/smartlabs, they may be able to save you headaches."}
{"Author": "Mark K. Sullivan", "Date": "on August 19, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "You cannot replace a hub without re-entering all of your devices", "Text": "Inability to replace a hub without rebuilding your data is totally unacceptable. Returning this unit. As long as I am starting over, I'm not going to make the Insteon mistake again."}
{"Author": "shawn Thompson", "Date": "on August 18, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works great. This needs to be plugged directly in the ...", "Text": "Works great. This needs to be plugged directly in the outlet, I had difficulty with it connecting to the devices when it was plugged into a power strip."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on August 10, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "So far this works great", "Text": "I had been looking for a solution to turning on and off some lights installed on our house for the outside that do not have switches. The insteon hub and switches are working great and easy to use. The app on the iPhone is nice. I have even added a few interior lights so we can turn them on for the dogs if we get home late. The mini remote was not a very good item. i had to return it. I recommend using the hub for sure."}
{"Author": "Mr. And Mrs. Hawks", "Date": "on August 5, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Unsafe And Unreliable Junk", "Text": "Bought 2 kits, one from Walmart on clearance and another from Costco on clearance just got the 2 outlets and a backup HUB. Without a Google home for voice control, this device would be useless, as the app interface is so slow and clunky, you'd rather get up and manually turn on/off whatever it is faster. A lot of the time Google would say \"an unexpected error occurred\" and you'd have to repeat the command again for it to work. Here we are just under 2 years later and a couple outlet/sensor failures, the hub literally blew up... A cap must've been slowly leaking or something, because all the solder joints were rusted and there was white smoke residue everywhere around a burnt spot on the PCB. Had been transitioning to a Z-WAVE Plus ecosystem anyway over this year that has preformed flawlessly and can communicate across all kinds of open source platforms or different HUBs of your choosing. Bottom line, stay far away from this awful product."}
{"Author": "dusty warner", "Date": "on August 4, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Four Stars", "Text": "works ok"}
{"Author": "MJD-Wyo", "Date": "on August 1, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "R.I.P. 32 month lifespan", "Text": "Really disappointed in this hub. I purchased in Nov '15 and it died two weeks ago. Lasted 32 months.\nThis sits on a shelf in air conditioned room and dead already? This has got to be design problem.\nI have 2-way repeaters installed on mtn tops for PD, SO, Fire that have been operating for 15 years.\nPrevious to this, had home control running on PC with USB Link module. It lasted about 3 or 4 years.\nReally wish there was alternative for Insteon devices. Still researching before I'll buy another hub."}
{"Author": "Nate", "Date": "on July 31, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Dead", "Text": "Worked fine but now dead after almost three years."}
{"Author": "Herr Hoffmann", "Date": "on July 25, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "New device, ancient software, customer service? What is it?", "Text": "Extremely old firmware on a NEW device, software is clunky, unresponsive and slow. Support is difficult to reach and work with. I could say support is nonexistent. Save your time and money, shop around and stay away from Insteon products."}
{"Author": "urch4ever", "Date": "on July 21, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Thank You"}
{"Author": "peter", "Date": "on July 17, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "works great. lets me set schedules for a bunch of ...", "Text": "works great. lets me set schedules for a bunch of lights outside and inside too."}
{"Author": "Ronnie Cooper", "Date": "on July 14, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great products", "Text": "I\u2019ve been using Insteon products for over 5 years (20 devices and 6 cameras) and it works without flaw (assuming you have set the units up correctly and are within range). The complaints on thier products seem to be people who don\u2019t have the time or patience to set the products correctly."}
{"Author": "Robert E. Runstein", "Date": "on June 29, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Controls X10 modules!!!", "Text": "Not sure if this is documented anywhere online, but you can control your existing X10 modules with the Insteon Hub. Downside is that it appears that only Insteon modules can be used with Scenes, but you can ***almost*** replicate this functionality by setting all X10 modules you want to trigger on/off to the same house and unit code and then set a schedule on one of them. For anyone tired of trying to make due with the European version of Active Home Pro program and CM15A transceiver for their existing X10 modules this is a welcome (and more reliable) surprise."}
{"Author": "Dimebag", "Date": "on June 29, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Do yourself a favor- Avoid at all costs.", "Text": "If I could give this product a zero, I would.\n\nI purchased a 2245-222 hub off of Amazon with pre-1014 firmware which supported X10 (NO JOKE... 100% on that. The APP even has an X10 device setup - which worked with my X10 devices). One day I took notice that the Hub lost its X10 capability, as Insteon updated the firmware. Thanks for the heads up... SO INFURIATING TO BUY A PRODUCT AND HAVE THAT PRODUCT'S FEATURES ELIMINATED!!! Was this a sick joke? Really?\n\nI originally bought the Hub because the Hub was advertised as X10 capable... conveniently Insteon's website literature changed after my purchase.\n\nI'm so angry that you should look out for my Insteon devices on ebay, after I rip them out of my home. Will be at a steep discount.\n\nI will never buy, nor recommend, and will even discourage people from buying INSTEON (A.K.A GARBAGE).\n\nHAVE A NICE DAY!!!"}
{"Author": "a guy", "Date": "on June 27, 2018", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "It\u2019s a love/hate relationship", "Text": "I\u2019ve had the insteon hub and various modules for about 3.5 years now. There are some unique things about insteon that get it closer to 3 stars than 2 for my application.\n\nFirst the good... if your looking for a decent way to schedule lighting, this is easy and offers some good options. You can even buy hard wired light switches to control anything in your house that uses a light switch. That\u2019s the main reason I purchased Insteon over others, and it\u2019s been nice to be able to control ceiling lights/fans with schedules as well as Alexa. Also this is likely more cost effective if you\u2019re trying to automate an entire house as opposed to one or two lamps.\n\nThe bad... Alexa control is pretty hit or miss, she has trouble finding devices 1/4 of the time and says the device isn\u2019t responding. That could be Alexa\u2019s fault, hard to tell, because when I use the insteon app it will control the device just fine. Overall the base unit signal to each module is pretty weak, so if you have a decent size house with a 200 amp breaker panel you will need a range extender or two. The App is pretty clunky and I feel it could be better, but to be fair it does it\u2019s job well enough. One of the hard wired dimmer switches I had craped out and I had to buy a new one, which sucked because they aren\u2019t cheap and you have to rewire the switch which is something I\u2019d prefer not to have to do considering the price of the modules.\n\nOverall, if you\u2019re a DIYer that\u2019s tech savvy and have some extra money you\u2019re willing to spend so you don\u2019t have to get off the couch to hit a switch, then you should be able to handle it. I haven\u2019t tried any other systems, but I would think there are probably some more user friendly options out there if you just need a plug in lamp controller or two. If you\u2019re trying to control an entire house, this is likely cheaper, but you\u2019ll definitely need some patience."}
{"Author": "Mary Darr", "Date": "on June 27, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Terrible", "Text": "This is not a good system. Hub will die after 2 years. You will not be able to use the same ID for a replacement hub.\n\nYou will not be able to manually operate lights after creating a schedule for the lights.\n\nEpic fail."}
{"Author": "Traxx", "Date": "on June 24, 2018", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works", "Text": "It works but seriously, no way to back up? Big-time fail. Insteon has a lot less problems than z-wave but had I known there was no backup / restore I would have bought z-wave. Equipment fails, why lose all data when it does?"}
{"Author": "TechLover", "Date": "on June 22, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "One Star", "Text": "Had to return it, it didn't work."}
{"Author": "FritzDelGato", "Date": "on June 21, 2018", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Keep your receipt until the warranty expires!", "Text": "Had to buy this one as a replacement because manufacturer will not honor warranty claim without proof of purchase. Like everyone keeps receipts for a $100 purchase. I registered on their web site when I purchased, and they should be able to tell when I first started using their product from their server logs... sheesh!\n\nIf you search the internet, you will see that these apparently have problems with capacitors that crap out."}
{"Author": "Gregory", "Date": "on June 20, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Insteon is garbage!", "Text": "Garbage!\n3rd one that died within 90 days!\n\nDon\u2019t buy!!!\n\nYou have been warned..."}
{"Author": "J. Sink", "Date": "on June 19, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Run, don't walk away from Insteon.", "Text": "I've owned two of these pieces of garbage and they've both broken in under a year. No hyperbole, the software is the worst I've ever used. Shame I'm stuck with all these insteon switches. If you're considering going with programmable smart home devices, run don't walk away from Insteon."}
{"Author": "L. R. EVANS", "Date": "on June 15, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Hub replacement procedure is archaic, time consuming and support does not help.", "Text": "My Insteon Hub died, blown capacitor and transformer. I ordered this one to replace it. Insteon web site says you have to delete all your devices and your online account in order to install a new hub. With my hub down, the app will not connect to do that. So now you have to contact them to do it for you. I sent three email and am still waiting for them to delete the original account and the devices so I can connect the new hub to my devices. I gave up and ordered Wemo devices to replace the Insteon. I will eat the cost of the new hub and be done with it."}
{"Author": "Marcelino", "Date": "on June 13, 2018", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "No way to backup and restore hub programming.", "Text": "I have been using Insteon products for many years and in general I have been happy with the product. I purchased this hub because my original hub stopped working, totally dead. When I received this one to replace the failed one I found out that in order to setup the new hub I would have to start from scratch. Yes, you can't just login to your account and add a new hub. There is no way to restore from a backup or anything. If I only had a couple of devices that would be fine but I have around 20 devices around the house, no easy task to go re-install again. After searching the web I found that there is a capacitor that fails on the control board. I was able to replace the capacitor and my old hub came back to life.\nI have contacted Insteon support and asked that they provide some method to backup the hub so that if needed one can restore to a new one. So far NOTHING! Since the communications protocol used by Insteon is proprietary, they are the only ones making these products. I am now in the process of looking for alternative solutions that use a more open standard and that is supported by several vendors.\nOn the bright side, this does work very well with the Amazon Echo and having voice command of my lights is very handy.\nHope this helps."}
{"Author": "ConsumerAdvocate", "Date": "on June 8, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I think I have multiple hubs until they are no longer needed. Plus Linksys pushed Mo-Mimo which Apple does not support.", "Text": "Is interoperable for now until Google decides to make their new Google/Alexa type product that are enhanced beyong your Alexa,or Google models version."}
{"Author": "CA Guy", "Date": "on June 6, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Insteon Hub just works.", "Text": "Insteon finally has a hub that just works. Easy to set up using their mobile app. A great way to configure a RemoteLinc handheld, which are normally very tedious."}
{"Author": "PaulM2", "Date": "on May 29, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "WARNNG 2: AVOID THIS PROTOCOL AT ALL COSTS", "Text": "WARNING 2: Unless you have a large house, and plan to place Insteon devices throughout (e.g., on the other side of walls, out in the garage, etc.), DO NOT WASTE YOUR TIME AND MONEY WITH THIS PROTOCOL. It has more problems working with Alexa than I could have ever have imagined. I've had to call customer service on EVERY INSTEON DEVICE I purchased (switches, hub, thermostats). Customer Service LITERALLY told me there was an update pending that would resolve the issues with Alexa but turns out, after a follow-up call, THAT THERE WAS NEVER ANY UPDATE. Look, I don't know if I've ever negatively reviewed something purchased from Amazon, but I feel obligated to caution folks: being mislead has really ticked me off I must say. Apart from my emotions on this, the advice holds true to use another platform like Samsung (i.e., Z-Wave or Zigbee) if you have a \"regular person's\" size house (wink-wink)."}
{"Author": "Benjamin Chrysler", "Date": "on May 26, 2018", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "love/hate relationship with Insteon products, and it's time to say goodbye", "Text": "I have a love/hate relationship with Insteon products. When they work, they are great. The trick is getting them to work. Hub died after 2 years. In-wall switches and plug-in modules died sometimes as early as 6 months others lasted a couple years. For the in-warranty deaths, customer service was great.\n\nFor automation/hacking, their cloud API is OK, but I found it to be slower than I like. I resorted to using their serial interface locally, but it's not widely supported and rather cryptic. Google Assistant support was a nice recent addition though.\n\nI'm going to try jumping ship to Lutron Caseta products. They seem more widely used, and they have a mix of dimmers that work with the variety of LED type lights that California Title 24 requires."}
{"Author": "Michael F.", "Date": "on May 26, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Four Stars", "Text": "relatively problem free"}
{"Author": "Fred L Ballou Jr", "Date": "on May 25, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Still working great. 5-25-2018"}
{"Author": "eldon ward", "Date": "on May 23, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great purchase!", "Text": "Used the hub to sinc wall switches with Alexa. Great purchase!"}
{"Author": "EddieK", "Date": "on May 8, 2018", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Three Stars", "Text": "I like Insteon stuff, but one of the light modules stopped working after a month..."}
{"Author": "Anon", "Date": "on May 7, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Loved Gift", "Text": "Bought this and the echo dot for a girlfriend and she loves it."}
{"Author": "Kiki", "Date": "on April 30, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "THE 800 tech support # was USELESS, and there's been no reply via my email ...", "Text": "In less than 24 months of regular daily use, the HUB HAS DIED. THE 800 tech support # was USELESS, and there's been no reply via my email inquiry for a replacement."}
{"Author": "Cliente Amazon", "Date": "on April 28, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Compre esta hub nueva y me la han mandado usada ...", "Text": "Compre esta hub nueva y me la han mandado usada (lo s\u00e9 porque la caja viene con reparaciones con celo,tambi\u00e9n las que vienen dentro guardando los cables) adem\u00e1s de que la hub debe de estar dada de alta en otra cuenta de insteon y no me deja escanear el c\u00f3digo QF d\u00e1ndome el error de la foto o eso es lo que entiendo despu\u00e9s de buscar durante horas y horas en foros y habiendo echo mil vueltas al estado de f\u00e1brica, Buy this new hub and I have sent it used (I know because the box comes with repairs with zeal, also those that come inside guarding the cables) in addition to the hub must be registered in another account insteon and not me let me scan the QF code giving me the error of the photo or that is what I understand after searching for hours and hours in forums and having made a thousand returns to the factory state"}
{"Author": "Lochan", "Date": "on April 27, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Shop around. Do your research.", "Text": "I have setup 5 insteon systems for family members and ALL have failed just a little bit after the 2 year mark. 1 system actually failed after the 1 year mark. All 5 homes are configured with an insteon hub, multiple dimming switches, water leak sensors, a few outlets, door sensors and a few bulbs. Imagine my surprise when the first unit went out and I had to re-enter ALL the original settings and scenes.\n\nAfter replacing these units and speaking with insteon about my options I was pretty turned off from the whole system. All they could offer was a discounted hub and I was told its refurbished.\n\nUnfortunately we were all heavily invested with insteon already. I am slowly removing components where they fail and will eventually look at other systems.\n\nFor what its worth I have a 15 year tech background and this stuff is all I do. While they are amazing when they do work, Its not worth the hassle, time and money.\n\n1. Support is difficult to reach and work with.\n2. Units are not designed to last at all, it seems there is known fault with the hubs and insteon has done nothing about it besides offer a \"discounted\" hub.\n3. software is clunky and slow. no options for migrating settings when you have to replace a hub."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on April 25, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "One Star", "Text": "can not hook this up a waste of money"}
{"Author": "Hizzonr", "Date": "on April 24, 2018", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Worked fine, and with Alexa", "Text": "Worked fine, and with Alexa, for 2 years and three months before it died. I thought that was short which is why I gave it a 3. If that is an average life for this device then perhaps it deserves a higher score."}
{"Author": "Ken Hubalik", "Date": "on April 23, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Insteon Hubs Are Undependable And Their Tech Support is Very Poor", "Text": "I have found this hub to be very undependable and their tech support to be very poor. The first of these Insteon hubs I purchased started beeping at me and was no longer accessible from the smartphone application. I bought a replacement hub rather than trying to find the support phone number. The new hub lasted 7 months before it started beeping at me and could no longer be accessed from the smartphone app. This time I decided to contact tech support and resolve the issue. After two time-wasting debug sessions they pronounced the unit broken and finally started an RMA process that took another 20 minutes because they kept putting me on hold. When they finally asked me to image the Amazon receipt and email it to them I reached the end of my rope. Not looking forward to having to repeat the onerous hub setup process yet again, I gave up on the product and company."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on April 17, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "One Star", "Text": "I need to return this item because it does not operate with my current security camera"}
{"Author": "nelson", "Date": "on April 12, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "great thank u"}
{"Author": "Ticobird", "Date": "on April 11, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Be careful where you purchase Insteon products", "Text": "This is a useful product for automating electrical appliances such as unswitched outdoor landscape lights that require daily scheduling for turning on and off. It works as advertised. I gave the Insteon Hub 5 Stars but I would like to point out that the Insteon 2 Year Warranty only applies to purchases made through a retailer like Best Buy, Smarthome.com or Amazon.com. It does not apply to purchases made on Ebay.com because Insteon cannot verify if the product is a new purchase or a refurbished purchase. You can purchase Insteon Hubs cheaper on Ebay but doing so negates the Insteon 2 Year Warranty. I know this because my Insteon Hub died within the 2 Year Warranty period. At least Insteon gave me approximately a 50% discount for purchasing another through Smarthome over the phone since I was a verified previous customer. By the way, I will have to delete the Insteon phone app, reinstall the phone app, recreate my Insteon Account, add my Insteon devices and link it to the new hub."}
{"Author": "Joey125", "Date": "on April 10, 2018", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Quality of product diminished if you're not already invested stay away", "Text": "died in 5 month. would be a decent product it had its issues but made due until it decided to just die. Insteon support is now way harder to reach from when i first got my first hub in 2013.."}
{"Author": "J. gibson", "Date": "on April 9, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Device lasted less than three years. Warranty is only ...", "Text": "Device lasted less than three years. Warranty is only for two years. A simple search of the internet showed that this is a known defect having to do with a capacitor that is known to fail"}
{"Author": "Thomas P", "Date": "on April 8, 2018", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Two Stars", "Text": "Works great, however cannot control legacy X10 devices with Alexa, which was whole intent of upgrading from older hub."}
{"Author": "Thomas A. Miano", "Date": "on April 7, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "If you aren\u2019t committed to Insteon for home automation don\u2019t buy this!", "Text": "These Insteon hubs are garbage, I on my 4th unit and the most current one lasted 3 years. The only reason I keep replacing them is that my house is loaded with insteon devices. If I knew what I know today I wouldn\u2019t automate my house with Insteon.\nAlthough when they work it works well."}
{"Author": "Todd Decker", "Date": "on April 7, 2018", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "When it works, it works well. But, the long term reliability of the Insteon hub is questionable and a huge headache to replace", "Text": "These devices have a history of failing and when they do, you're stuck. On-line forums indicate that many people have had their units fail from one to three years after they installed them and this problem has been persisting since 2014 up to the present. While the two year warranty might help you get a replacement at no cost, it is still a major headache and undertaking to replace your old hub with a new one. If your hub fails you need to delete all your account and all your settings, schedules, scenes, devices and start all over again.\n\nI gave it two stars cause when it works it works pretty reliably with Amazon Echo and the smart phone app which is very cool. But you will find that if you really use the hub to automate your home and your unit fails... you could spend many many hours reprogramming your entire household back to what you had before a failure. I'm heavily invested in the Insteon system so I had to buy a replacement, but I am very disappointed that I will be spending the better part of a Saturday running around my house programming all my devices from scratch. Insteon needs to improve the hardware reliability AND improve the software so all your account setting can be readily ported to a new hub in the then RARE case where the hub fails. Very disappointed."}
{"Author": "Michael", "Date": "on April 3, 2018", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Insteon vs ZB?", "Text": "I've had this since 9/15, and I'm writing about my experience with it. The App is poorly made, in my opinion. Quite confusing going from one setting to another. The plus side of the Insteon system is that Insteon outlet can control and dim your lamps, which you would typically need a dimmer control if you went with a ZB solution. Scene was great, as it can automate based on your settings. Basically, all things would work well if, well, they're configured properly and you no longer need to add anything to your setup. However, in my case where my hub completely crapped out on me, well, good luck buddy as none of your Insteon switches/dimmers will work. That's one great thing about ZB, as there's a wide range of support, as seen in Amazon Echo Plus and Samsung Smartthings. I'm beginning to migrate over to ZB right now, and I wished that I had done that before I bought the Insteon setup. Only thing I wished for was the ZB outlets can double as a dimmer and outlet, which I have yet to find one."}
{"Author": "Joe", "Date": "on April 3, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Excellent Product"}
{"Author": "Elizabeth", "Date": "on April 2, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great for whole home lighting and doesn't interfere with our Wi-Fi", "Text": "We have this working together with Alexa to control whole home lighting scenes (wake up, evening, good night). Our neighbors tried doing the same with smart switches that are wi-fi based but ended up spending hundreds of dollars in extending their wi-fi signals because the signals didn't get to where they had wall switches. We love our wi-fi which is why I chose Insteon. It uses some blend of radio and electrical wire signals to get around walls and travel really far. Also, the Insteon switches all repeat signals so the more you add, the stronger things get - exact opposite with wi-fi switches."}
{"Author": "Ali", "Date": "on April 1, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Solid hardware terrible support and software", "Text": "This product has solid hardware they are not cheap however their technical support is non existent. For a week their server is down and tech support tells me they are working on it. There is no local control everything goes through their server if you use this hub. Hence when their server is down you can't control your system through local network."}
{"Author": "R. Knowlton", "Date": "on March 31, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Mine died like many others 27 months after Purchase(24 month royalty)", "Text": "Mine died like many others 27 months after Purchase(24 month royalty). Now the only solution Insteon has designed is to go to every device, do a factory reset, then buy a new hub and painfully relink every switch and plug. This is both ludicrous design and quality. Very disappointing!!!."}
{"Author": "Paul D. Carlucci", "Date": "on March 30, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Insteon is dead to me. They're just unreliable, ...", "Text": "Insteon is dead to me. They're just unreliable, I've switched over to Z-Wave Plus. This particular setup is twitchy and certain things, but at least it hasn't died yet, unlike every other Insteon product in my house.\n\nThe particularly infuriating problem with it was I had a wire in dimmer that I could control from the app but never from the web API or the website on the open internet. Support couldn't help.\n\nAnyway, the capacitor in that wire unit eventually puked over everything inside and it joined its friends in the landfill."}
{"Author": "Tom O. Pritchett", "Date": "on March 26, 2018", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Very disappointed in this new hub", "Text": "Several years ago, I installed an Insteon hub, and a few water leak sensors. One of those sensors saved our basement when we were on vacation, and I was a very happy camper. But over the years, I was frustrated by the many limitations with the hub, like lack of geo-fencing, Google Home linkage, and basic if/then logic that come standard in other hubs. I saw this new Insteon hub on a giant sale, and decided to upgrade. Installing the new Insteon hub was a giant pain. I couldn't save my old device/scene/room setup, and had to manually re-enter everything (1/2 day wasted). Worse, when I tested several of my old sensors, I found that neither the old or new hub would detect a low battery state. I've had a bunch of mini-bricks in my house for months/years. Now that it's installed, I'm getting lots of false positives from a motion sensor, and it keeps losing connectivity with my router. And, reading the reviews, it seems many have complained about the reliability of this hub. Yikes!! I've sent it back, and since moved on to the SmartThings hub, which supports a ton of ZigBee and Zwave sensors, and is a lot easier to setup and use."}
{"Author": "M. Fields", "Date": "on March 24, 2018", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Two Stars", "Text": "Wish these would last more than 2 years....."}
{"Author": "Carlos Lopez", "Date": "on March 22, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Stay away!!!", "Text": "Unreliable. I only use it for one single light switch, and still half of the time it is not working."}
{"Author": "Mac Mead", "Date": "on March 21, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easy To Add, Fun To Use, Don\u2019t Use for mission critical", "Text": "I\u2019ve had the insteon products like other users for a long time. I had the old wall plug hub in the old house and now the new hub in my new house. I control lots of lights, pool pump, fans, water detectors - I guess 30 devices all in all. With so many devices talking and transmitting the network is rock solid. If the hub gives a command, it is always followed.\n\nI find the design of the hub ok. Mine died like others and after reading the boards I bought a bag of C7 switching CAPs and replaced the C7 and all is right with the world. I measured the one that came out. It had only 10% of the strength as the one I put in. Now I have 200 years worth of CAPs. I think the duty cycle for the C7 CAP is pretty hard. But I didn\u2019t loose all my programming and all is cool.\n\nI find the software functional - that\u2019s about it. We should be able to use our own icons and change colors. What we have is boring and for my old eyes I can\u2019t tell the difference between one button and the next if I choose the same graphic. The house-rooms-scenes thing works ok. I see other users complaining that they can\u2019t set two scenes to start at the same time, like sunset. What\u2019s the big deal? You just creat a sunset scene and put everything it it you want. Then if you want things to turn off, say 11 pm and then sunrise you create an 11 pm off scene and a sunrise off scene and put the devices you want in there. I think people over think things sometimes.\n\nThe hacking bothers me. I read that it\u2019s possible. Is it true? Smarthome should tell us. Smarthome updates the software automatically from time to time. No action on my part. I never notice. Everything is controlled through the internet. So if that goes down, your phones and iPads won\u2019t be able to control it. But that\u2019s not often. I also think that we use Smarthome\u2019s servers. Does that mean that Smarthome knows what all of it\u2019s products are doing?\n\nAdding devices is a snap, especially the more you add. Push a button, hear a beep, follow the directions on your iPhone.\n\nAll in all I appreciate its design and how it controls lights, keeps track of when sunrise and sunset is, and just works .. except when you loose C7,which is every 2-3years."}
{"Author": "JP7570", "Date": "on March 19, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easy but requires completely re-entering all your devices.", "Text": "If you've worked with the previous Instead Hub version, this one will be a bit easier (no need for reconfiguring your router for port fowarding). But a basic gripe about this Hub - you will have to manually re-enter every one of your devices, scenes, and rooms. Insteon has no provision for saving the previous setup on its app and transferring it over to a new Hub. Very poor design on Insteon's part."}
{"Author": "Michael S Dutcher", "Date": "on March 19, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Uses RF and powerline (Dual-Band) so always reliable communication between devices"}
{"Author": "kim", "Date": "on March 17, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I cant get it to work and now I missed ...", "Text": "I cant get it to work and now I missed the return time period so so unhappy with this darn things"}
{"Author": "Caesar", "Date": "on March 12, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I returned it....", "Text": "I order this hub looking to streamline my Smart Home capabilities.\nMy Ethernet connection is upstair... after countless time attempting to connect, Frustration overcame me.\nThe next day, I was determine to connect.... this unit doesn't read wifi,\nYou can connect by item identification, however the Item must be close to the Hub or you can purchase a Extender.\nIt became Frustrating for me. I returned it to Amazon for a refund"}
{"Author": "Alan K.", "Date": "on March 9, 2018", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "My issue is the setup procedure and the fact that ...", "Text": "My issue is the setup procedure and the fact that the Insteon account is tied to a device, not to the user. I had to purchase a new hub to replace another 2245-222 hub that went dead after 2 years, 2 months. When I installed my new hub and tried to create an account, it would not allow me to set up the account with the same email address as was associated with the account for my previous hub. The only way to access my existing account is through my old hub which no longer works, so I have no way of deleting the account. I am now in the middle of a multi-day odyssey, exchanging emails with Insteon support to have them delete my old account. From an architecture and user experience standpoint this makes no sense."}
{"Author": "aw1200", "Date": "on March 4, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I had no problems setting up my hub and adding ...", "Text": "I had no problems setting up my hub and adding 18 devices - all Insteon switches. But ... when I tried to add Scenes, it was a nightmare. I wanted to set up 4 Scenes - 3 groups of 6 each, and one \u201cAll Lights\u201d Scene. Setting up each of the Scenes takes forever, and I was continually asked to Press and Hold the Set button for each device over and over. Eventually I got the first three Scenes set up, and programmed test schedules for each. On the first Scene, only 2 of the 6 lights come on and off. On the other 2 Scenes, NONE of the lights come on! I haven\u2019t even started on the \u201cAll Lights\u201d Scene - it would probably take several days to set it up, and it is unlikely that it would work anyway, given my experience so far. I can\u2019t understand why setting up the Scenes should be such a nightmare when all of the 18 individual devices work perfectly."}
{"Author": "D. N. Knisely", "Date": "on March 2, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Terrible Insteon app, but the service works beautifully with Alexa or Google Home once configured.", "Text": "Finally integrates beautifully with Google Home (as well as Alexa). This is the hub you want for Google Home or Alexa, not the more expensive model. Insteon is now awesome with either ecosystem (Alexa or Google Home). -1 star for terrible app from Insteon required to configure the hub and for Insteon's horrendous cloud service. But, once set up, works beautifully."}
{"Author": "dontusemyrealname", "Date": "on March 1, 2018", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Three Stars", "Text": "Works great with app, has occasional issues with Alexa, but for the price not bad."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on February 28, 2018", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Three Stars", "Text": "lots of problems"}
{"Author": "RICHARD RITTERMANN", "Date": "on February 27, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Tried everything. Called support. Did what they suggested ...", "Text": "Tried everything. Called support. Did what they suggested. One minute it works. Next minute it does not. Router and hub were 15 feet from the switches. Switched phases per their suggestion. Even put the switches on the same breaker as the hub. I am tired of wasting my time and money.\nDo not buy!"}
{"Author": "Tim_M", "Date": "on February 27, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "This works", "Text": "This was a replacement for one that died. Works ok. I need to be able to control devices from my phone and this works."}
{"Author": "Mike E.", "Date": "on February 25, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Try it you\u2019ll like it", "Text": "I\u2019m sold on Insteon Products especially after all the frustration that X-10 caused me years ago. This system just plain works and for anyone needing or wanting to set up and use a Fanlinc this system is a \u2018must-have\u2019"}
{"Author": "David Gorrell", "Date": "on February 25, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easy installation and integration with Amazon Echo", "Text": "I have had a mix of X-10 and Insteon switches for controlling lights and appliances for many years. The X-10, being no longer supported, are reaching end of life. In addition, I thought I would like to take advantage of the Amazon Echo interface for the lights.\nThe Insteon hub is plugged into my Comcast modem which has also hosts a Linksys Velop router.\nSetup for the Insteon Hub was painless using the iPhone App. In just a few minutes I had linked my existing Insteon switches to the hub and to my iPhone. I then used the Alexa App \"Smart Home\" section to connect the Insteon devices and quickly had voice command of the lights for On/Off and intensity. One set of lights indicated it was connected but wouldn't actually respond to Echo or iPhone inputs, but I soon realized that was due to the light having a \"3-way\" setup and I had linked the Slave switch instead of the Master. After correcting that error all worked as planned.\nI am pleased enough to start ordering Insteon swiitches and plug-ins to replace my X-10 switches. Many reviews complain of the short service life of the Insteon gear. In my experience, with 4 wall switches, I have had no problem in around 10 years of service. I will update this review after installing the additional switch gear."}
{"Author": "William K. Nonidez", "Date": "on February 25, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Bought two and had to return both within 6 months.", "Text": "I have purchased two of these hubs to use with Alexa and have had to return both within 6 months because they completely stopped functioning. I was able to return both for replacements and am now on my second set. I don\u2019t think I would by these hubs again. I suggest you look for an alternative."}
{"Author": "gadgetguy", "Date": "on February 23, 2018", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "If I didn't need it, I would have bought it.", "Text": "I wish I didn't need it. Often loses connection, even though hard wired in. There was a known issue with previous model that would brick it completely, making it effectively dead. Another company with bad customer service."}
{"Author": "Charles Mineau", "Date": "on February 22, 2018", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Two Stars", "Text": "This product needs to work better. Tec support is good."}
{"Author": "Mike Foley", "Date": "on February 20, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Set it up and go", "Text": "Like it installs quick"}
{"Author": "G. Woods", "Date": "on February 17, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "very easy to use", "Text": "I've had this for about 5 months now and so far works perfectly.....even one outlet is outdoors in the damp air (no direct water contact). I also bought another brand of outlets that doesn't require it's own hub. So far I haven't been able to use the other brand because getting the app to work has been chalenging. The Insteon app is by comparison, very easy to use."}
{"Author": "Ron", "Date": "on February 13, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Very happy with Insteon Switches", "Text": "The Insteon switches and Hub work great together. Pairing each added insteon device is easy and pretty quick. It allows you to have 3 and 4 way arrays too (although it's a little tricky). I personally haven't had any issues so far. Overall very happy with the Insteon switches."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on February 12, 2018", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "There may be better hubs out there", "Text": "I've been using this hub for my home automation working with Amazon alexa. Unfortunately the hub appears to be finicky. The last update that they pushed out has created a problem and now the Hub works when it feels like it's working."}
{"Author": "Mark Scheider", "Date": "on February 12, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Terrible. Terrible", "Text": "Terrible. Terrible. Terrible product. First Hub only lasted a year. And we bought a replacement and it wouldn\u2019t work with our existing system. A Sonos is so easy to set up. It just works. This is the opposite. Terrible user interface. DO NOT BUY THIS PRODUCT!!!"}
{"Author": "M att", "Date": "on February 12, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great product great price", "Text": "Great product great price"}
{"Author": "Jim Sands", "Date": "on February 6, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great starter home automation kit", "Text": "Best investment in home automation. Works well with Alexa"}
{"Author": "Ken Mitchell", "Date": "on February 5, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Doesn't work with Alexa", "Text": "I had to return it and get a refund. Just wouldn't work with Alexa."}
{"Author": "Martin Ennis", "Date": "on February 4, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "If you buy this, you're making a mistake!", "Text": "I wish I could give this a negative 5 stars. Hours of wasted money and time. Don't Buy!\nI purchased all of my home automation peripheral devices before I bought this piece of crap. What a mistake. I never got the hub to connect to my home wifi. I tried several different routers and networks. As far as I can tell, it fails to register as an IP device, and is therefore, not assigned an IP address.\nInsteon tech support is worthless. I finally gave up and sent it back.\nAmazon issued a full refund on the kit. But I'm stuck with $400 worth of insteon devices and nothing to pair to."}
{"Author": "Matt", "Date": "on January 31, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Control everything with your iPhone and Alexa voice-control!", "Text": "I love controlling all the Insteon devices from my iPhone and Amazon Alexa. The previous owner of the house installed all Insteon switches. It took me a couple hours to register about a hundred devices to the hub with my Iphone. Now I have timed lights and fountains coming on, christmas lights automatically turning on. I was in Spain the other day and could see the status of all the lights in the house in California!"}
{"Author": "Deb S", "Date": "on January 31, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I hope that the Insteon Home Control Starter Kit pleases ...", "Text": "I hope that the Insteon Home Control Starter Kit pleases my son. I have no idea how it is used. This was an item on his Christmas wish so I got it for him for his birthday."}
{"Author": "Cordob\u00e9s", "Date": "on January 31, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Terrible customer service and terrible product with such short lifespan", "Text": "Buyer beware! My hub stopped working after less than two years of usage. It went completely out; the led light won't even power in the unit. So what do I do now? If I buy a new one now, I will have to delete all my scenes and reset all of my switches and plugs. Basically, I need to redo the set up as each unit in my house was new. I read a comment here on Amazon where a customer was having the same issue and the \"manufacturer\" responded saying that they offered a fast 2-day repair service. Well, that was a lie. When I contacted them directly they sent me this email below discouraging me to do the repair. The closest thing to help they offered was to take a screenshot of the hub ID and then somehow they will help me re-do the device list. Terrible customer service and terrible product with such short lifespan. I will try to get a better hub that works with their switches.\n\nEmail from them:\n\nThank you for contacting Smart Home.\n\nWith regards to your email, we are sorry for the issue that you have been going through and we will be happy to assist you on the same.\n\nWe are here by to inform you that, we only have the repair option when the customer is installed more than 40 devices to the Hub and for your information repair option takes more than 20 days to resolve.\n\nHowever, please go through the below documentation for setting up the new Hub, if the old Hub gets defective.\n\nIn order to register new Hub with the same user name and password or with the different one, you have to delete the account which is associated with old Hub.\n\nFor your information, you do not have an option to retain the Scenes or schedules from defective Hub but we can help you out with the device list and you can add the devices to new Hub with less time frame.\n\nSo, to delete the old Hub, we request you to attach the snap shot of old Hub Id to do the needful.\n\nHave a good day!\n\nRegards,\nJames."}
{"Author": "Nishant Shah", "Date": "on January 31, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "the insteon hub has been great to me", "Text": "As of right now, almost 3 months in to it, the insteon hub has been great to me. I love all insteon products and convenience of using it. I can control everything through app. I m hesitating to buy alexa to have, voice controlled feature. But, eventually, will do that as well."}
{"Author": "Mike", "Date": "on January 29, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "One Star", "Text": "It would not work on my 5 years old Insteon switches"}
{"Author": "Xalthe", "Date": "on January 27, 2018", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "It works most of the time. I had an ...", "Text": "It works most of the time. I had an issue a couple weeks ago where it didn't seem to be connected. None of my other network devices had any issues with connectivity, so I did a hard reset and it seemed to fix itself. That issue hasn't come back, though. Would have rated 4 stars otherwise."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on January 25, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "If Hub fails, you need to start over from scratch!", "Text": "I have been a big fan of Insteon and have it installed throughout my house. Unfortunately, last week my Insteon Hub died and I had to order a new one. Fair enough. Electronics sometimes fail.\n\nHowever, when I tried to install the new Hub, it said \"unable\". When I called Insteon support, I was told that if the Hub failed, the entire system programming needs to be redone -- scenes, etc.\n\nThis is obviously absurd, but I was unable to get any further with their technical support. I will be calling a Lutron installer tomorrow with amazement and sorrow."}
{"Author": "Daniel", "Date": "on January 25, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Very good product"}
{"Author": "Steven Hockstein", "Date": "on January 24, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "The base system is great. the system works well", "Text": "The base system is great. the system works well. The extra switches are too expensive. Other systems are more competitively priced and I think there should be package deals for multiple switches."}
{"Author": "Scotty D", "Date": "on January 23, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Amateur Design Flaws = Huge Inconvenience for You", "Text": "If your hub dies and you replace it, under warranty or otherwise, you have to delete your existing Insteon account and manually add all of your devices to your new hub\n\nIf you have more than one hub associated with your account and one of them is offline, you cannot access any of your hubs.\n\nMight be the worst architectural design I've ever seen. Avoid these amateurs and go with SmartThings instead."}
{"Author": "Scotty D", "Date": "on January 23, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Amateur Design Flaws = Huge Inconvenience for You", "Text": "If your hub dies and you replace it, under warranty or otherwise, you have to delete your existing Insteon account and manually add all of your devices to your new hub\n\nIf you have more than one hub associated with your account and one of them is offline, you cannot access any of your hubs.\n\nMight be the worst architectural design I've ever seen. Avoid these amateurs and go with SmartThings instead."}
{"Author": "Scotty D", "Date": "on January 23, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Critical Design Flaws = Huge Inconveniences for You", "Text": "If your hub dies and you replace it, under warranty or otherwise, you have to delete your existing Insteon account and manually add all of your devices to your new hub\n\nIf you have more than one hub associated with your account and one of them is offline, you cannot access any of your hubs.\n\nMight be the worst architectural design I've ever seen. Avoid these amateurs and go with SmartThings instead."}
{"Author": "Samantha Chang", "Date": "on January 23, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Alexa doesn\u2019t work with this. I\u2019ve gone through customer ...", "Text": "Alexa doesn\u2019t work with this. I\u2019ve gone through customer service several times now. Looking through the boards- it seems it\u2019s a problem with Alexa."}
{"Author": "John H.", "Date": "on January 21, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Great way to start moving to smart home."}
{"Author": "Sterling C. Poteat, III", "Date": "on January 19, 2018", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Bought it for a friend as a Christmas gift. ...", "Text": "Bought it for a friend as a Christmas gift. Friend could not get it to setup. Returned it for an Echo."}
{"Author": "Charles Johnstone", "Date": "on January 17, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works great out of the box", "Text": "Works great out of the box. This is a new item containing the Insteon Hub (#2245-222) and two Insteon Dual-Band LampLink Dimmers (#245D2). This set appears to have been created for Costco, as the packaging says \"additional items available at costco.com. The hub came with firmware #1006, but after an update, it has 1013 installed. Overall, this seems a great deal on these three components...the kit costs less than the Insteon Hub! So far, so good!"}
{"Author": "J. Albright", "Date": "on January 13, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Android App doesn't work and customer service escapes responsibility", "Text": "I have owned this product since 2014 and the android app does not remove any devices from scenes. So when you want to remove something from one of the scenes in your home you have to reset all of your devices to make sure you removed all the group ID from the joined devices. Worst of this is support has been giving me the run around for it for years. The sad part is support constantly calls each other liars as I will get confirmation of the problem as a \"known error\" and then another technician literally said \"you are the only one in the galaxy reporting this.\" I have escalated to supervisors only to continue to get conflicting information. The solution they are giving me at this time is to buy an Apple device and try that. I have never encountered customer service actually blaming others for known problems."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on January 12, 2018", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "seems to be unstable", "Text": "I wish I had looked around a little more before ordering this unit. Alexa seems to lose connection with the hub AT LEAST once a week and I have to go into my computer to turn the lights on or off or to dim them. It stops for no reason and then starts again for the same unknown reason. I'm hoping the Phillips Hue set I ordered for other lights will work better."}
{"Author": "Hisham El-Husseini", "Date": "on January 11, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "One Star", "Text": "Didnt even work. Can\u2019t get passed the configuration and I\u2019m upset that I have spent money on this product. Now I have to go through the hassle to send it back. Waste of money, waste of time."}
{"Author": "Markos Kashiouris", "Date": "on January 10, 2018", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Three Stars", "Text": "After two years, it just stopped working -- dead. The light turned off and not operational."}
{"Author": "Dieu Ly", "Date": "on January 8, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "This product is crap. I wish I never invested so much money ...", "Text": "You\u2019ve been warned don\u2019t do it. It only works sometimes... TPlink much cheaper and works. This product is crap. I wish I never invested so much money on Insteon in my house. I\u2019m going to have to change all my switches to get rid of this expensive junk."}
{"Author": "Dieu Ly", "Date": "on January 8, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "It would have been better off staying with my old manual switch", "Text": "If you want hear from Alexa \u201cThe Insteon hub is not responding\u201d this is the product for you. I have been using Insteon and TP-link for all the light switches in my house for the past 3 years. My Insteon is not so instant in its response, and that\u2019s when it works. It would have been better off staying with my old manual switch. On to the garage door opener once you use the app you will have to manually reset your garage door what a pain. Insteon is not ready for this IoT revolution. I wish I never brought this crap now I have go back and change all my switches back because what a waste of money and time. Believe me it\u2019s not a cheap project."}
{"Author": "ssr0822", "Date": "on January 8, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Your echo and Insteon solution", "Text": "If you have Insteon and echo, a must have"}
{"Author": "Garino", "Date": "on January 5, 2018", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "NO support for Insteon I/O Linc with Alexa", "Text": "Works good until I discovered that it doesn't support all Insteon devices. I added an Insteon I/O Linc to control a device but then discovered that the Insteon hub doesn't make the I/O Linc device visible to Alexa. So it can't be controlled by Alexa and the Echo Dot. Fail. I should've bought the ISY-994i instead."}
{"Author": "Rebecca Reuter", "Date": "on January 4, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "but so far I am very pleased. Here are a couple of tips", "Text": "I had an older hub 2242-222 and a fairly extensive Insteon installation but wanted the Amazon Echo support, so I got this kit to get the new hub and got the included wall modules for dirt cheap compared to the price of just the new hub alone. Given all the mixed reviews I was concerned, but so far I am very pleased. Here are a couple of tips:\n\n1) I kept the older 2242-222 hub to keep the X10 and HouseLinc support, but I completely removed the old app config on the cloud and deleted the account before installing the new hub. I did have to use HouseLinc to clean up some stranded device links after deleting the old app account.\n2) Then I installed the new hub, created a new account, and set everything up with the app.\n3) I used the iPhone app to do the setup and it went well. The Windows Phone app was too buggy to do setup and the Android app gets negative reviews so I did not even try it. So I used the iPhone app for setup, and am glad I did. Except for some long waits while setting up scenes, it was painless.\n4) I have a mix of old (no extended commands) and new devices, and had no problem at all using the old devices with the new hub. Setup of the old modules did require being physically at the devices (all wired-in switches) to push the setup button as instructed by the app to discover and configure them and create scenes.\n\nThe new hub either came with or immediately updated to the latest firmware version (1013 as of this writing) before I did the setup so maybe that is one reason I had no trouble.\n\nThe link to the Echo does not correctly show the scenes; it shows them, but as devices instead of scenes. I also created some groups in the Echo skill to mimic the scenes, so I'm not sure which it is using for voice commands, but it does work as intended (\"Alexa, turn on entry lights\" works, where entry lights is a scene and entry is a group.)"}
{"Author": "Jordan", "Date": "on January 1, 2018", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works! Until it doesn't.", "Text": "I bought this directly from Smarthome a couple years ago (and change) now. It died a month after its two year anniversary of running in my home. The warranty on it is 1 year. A stationary, set-it-and-forget-it device that has no moving parts and you never physically interact with it can just up and stop working. Pretty cool!\n\nIn the time that it was actually working, it made dealing with outlets and switches easier than some of the Windows-based automation programs. It allowed me to see those devices in Alexa once I bought one of those and the control from there was pretty slick. It's also nice that even with the hub dead (and sitting on my desk, unplugged), that the switches and outlets continue to work. Other systems don't do that. The downside of that nice fact is that if I were to buy a new hub, I'd have to redo every single thing about my setup. Considering you sign in with an account, that's pretty crazy that the configuration isn't stored somewhere.\n\nEither way, buy this if you have Insteon devices and want to control them without running software on your computer."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on January 1, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Poor Quality Control", "Text": "Just be aware that the product is made in China and is poor quality. Subject to burn out within two years. Slack quality control. Would go to the competition were it not for all the money I spent on sensors."}
{"Author": "wiconsumer", "Date": "on December 30, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Good product with some minor gotchas.", "Text": "I've purchased two of these. The second to replace one that died after two years. Overall, I have very happy with the Insteon products, but there are a few draw backs you should know about...\n\n1.) There is really no good web interface. They have a pretty robust REST API if you want to program one yourself, but there isn't a page to just go turn your stuff on and off. You pretty much are stuck with using phone/tablet apps.\n\n2.) My bridge died and their process for transitioning your devices and configuration is literally \"erase everything and start over\". That's completely unacceptable both technically and from a customer service perspective.\n\n3.) The hub seems to fail to execute scheduled scene events from time to time. I use mine to turn on/off outdoor lighting and such and occasionally it just fails so I come home to a dark driveway or my lights are on all day. Not a huge deal, but annoying.\n\n4.) The updated hubs are 120v ONLY. For most people this won't be a big deal, but I utilize mine behind a 230v UPS, so the new hub doesn't work for me without a transformer. I couldn't find any mention of this in the description, so the change of design (without incrementing the model) is annoying."}
{"Author": "G280", "Date": "on December 29, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Piece of S*^%", "Text": "Barely worked for a couple months. Pure junk. Interface through app is horrendous. Latest update killed all of my scenes. Do not buy this. You will regret it from day one."}
{"Author": "J.G.", "Date": "on December 28, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Hardware fails far too soon.", "Text": "Hardware needs improvement.\n\nThis unit seems to die for no obvious reason about as soon as the warranty runs out.\n\nThe system also needs the ability to back up your settings and devices this stores as you'll have to start from scratch when it dies next."}
{"Author": "Fred", "Date": "on December 27, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Watch out", "Text": "I have a huge Insteon network in my home. Hard to set up and a little clunky, but it nevertheless made handling holiday lights much easier than going around the house turning things on and off individually. Then my hub died--no lights, no action, and no service from Insteon. So I went out and bought another hub, which arrived dead. Tried different ethernet connections and different power plugs, but no luck. After a 20 minute hold with customer service, I learned that Insteon still has no answer other than they will take back the second (but not the first) defective hub. Internet posts suggest that dead hubs are not that unusual, but with a lot invested in Insteon switches, I feel more than a little let down."}
{"Author": "618618", "Date": "on December 26, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "All Devices Don\u2019t work with Alexa", "Text": "Door open and close sensors DO NOT WORK WITH voice alerts and Amazon Alexa!"}
{"Author": "Peter", "Date": "on December 25, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Three Stars", "Text": "Problems pairing with Alexa often."}
{"Author": "Eric Thompson", "Date": "on December 25, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Works as it should"}
{"Author": "Lawrence K.", "Date": "on December 24, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Poor Reliabilty", "Text": "I bought a hub directly from Smart Home and it worked great for almost 3 years. I am on my second hub purchased through Amazon and both worked for a couple weeks and then began to \u201chang\u201d with a red led showing. A reboot clears the hub however it hangs again in a couple days.\n\nI wonder if these are refurbished products.\n\nI am going to return and try one directly from Smart Home."}
{"Author": "Amazon Shopper", "Date": "on December 20, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "BRICKED with firmware update", "Text": "These guys don't know what they are doing. Got the firmware update (automatically, mind you) and it BRICKED my hub. I got an email notice that the update was coming, then the next day I heard some random chirping from the unit - assuming it was being updated - now dead. No lights. No network leds. Funny smell. Cable has power - checked it with a DMM. The update TOTALLY BRICKED the hub. Sent insteon a support request - I have no hope of getting a response. If you had yours bricked, please post here as a warning to others!"}
{"Author": "K. Knight", "Date": "on December 19, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great product but need Google Assistant/Home support.", "Text": "This is great. Outfitting my whole house with smart light switches and outlets.\nLost a star for not have Google Assistant/Home support. Using Harmony hub as my workaround.\n+1 Google Assist support now available."}
{"Author": "Lord Adam Spencer", "Date": "on December 18, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Four Stars", "Text": "Home is now digital"}
{"Author": "MS", "Date": "on December 16, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "There is no backup!", "Text": "If your hub fails, you will lose all of your devices, scenes and settings. Unbelievably there is no cloud backup, and not even a local USB backup option for the hub. Rookie mistake in this day and age Insteon!\n\nI\u2019ve used Insteon as my home control system for 4 years. I love the flexibility of being able to set it up myself, and the reliability of the switches and other devices. It just works. Until a few days ago when my hub stopped powering on. A bit of research highlighted a capacitor issue that can occur, so I suspect that\u2019s what it is. Insteon support were great, and are shipping me out a free replacement hub. But, I will have to set up all 45+ devices again, not to mention dozens of scenes! This will take a full weekend at least. There was an option to have my hub repaired (they basically take out the chip and put it in a new one), but that will take 5 weeks! And since my device controls all my lights, holiday lighting, garage doors and multiple sensors, I can\u2019t be without it for that period, so I have no option but to recreate everything. Insteon would have gotten a 5 star rating from me for sure, but this is such a big miss I\u2019m going to give it a 3. Hopefully they will add this feature soon or it really will limit the applicability to simple installations only."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on December 15, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Support is awful!", "Text": "Do not buy this thing. I have no idea what it would be like if it worked because Insteon support is absolutely terrible. I've never experienced such poor tech support in 20+ years of owning IT and other technical equipment. Insteon really needs to add some good quality technical support capability."}
{"Author": "Just another consumer", "Date": "on December 12, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Totally unreliable. OnlybBuy if you want to be switching it out every year.", "Text": "When we move into our home, we changed everything to use insteon because several things, they have good ideas and building a bunch of affordable devices and their headquarter is local to me. I've visited them and talk to one of their engineers about the future of the products as I'm an engineer myself. Quickly however, I discovered that there is a flaw in their devices. Things start to fail within a year, and subsequently I need to replace switches, etc within the 2-3 years that I have them. Initially, they are pretty amiable in terms of replacing the product. Soon, I discovered the front office/customer service in the factory store pretty much tells me to go to hell, in one conversation, they are saying, nothing last forever, you can't get things for free in this life. Well definitely I agree, nothing is free, while instead is cheaper than other home automation in the market, it's still pretty pricey and I also agree that nothing last forever but I'm hoping my light switch last more than 1 or 2 years because I have more than 30 light switches and sockets, and if I need to change several switches every other month, i'd rather go to other vendors who stands behind their products and is willing to respect that there's manufacturing defects. I mean I use my light switch just like a decent human would, press on and press off, heck i barely even touch them anymore with alexa. I do not put them in extreme situation or whatsoever, if it fails, it is NOT doing what it is supposed to.\n\nEnough of the rant about their other devices, the same with the the insteon central controller hub. It is just sitting there all pretty, taking in commands from what's left of my insteon switches and boom, suddenly my alexa said, can't contact insteon hub. I checked, surely enough, the front led light went dark, it's dead! After ~1 year of use. Since I do not ever want to visit their factory store again so this is the last straw. Adios Insteon!"}
{"Author": "KellySophieBently", "Date": "on December 11, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Insteon Hub stopped working", "Text": "MANY reviews of how this dies after, literally, 2 years and a few months - just after warranty is up. Mine just died 2 years, 1 month out. Had to order an entire new unit as I am not sure how to replace the C7 capacitor, which is what some of the forum participants said to do. Amazing that they can time this out so well in the manufacturing process to die right around this time. Planned obsolescence......the way of today!!"}
{"Author": "N. Koelkebeck", "Date": "on December 10, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love the control of my lights and", "Text": "Inexpensive way to add more modules to my Insteon system. Love the control of my lights and appliances"}
{"Author": "wander what you're doing?", "Date": "on December 9, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "CAUTION", "Text": "BUyer beware, the descriptions for each device are not always accurate. The set up is not as easy as the video indicates. When you contact the support number, there is a long wait, because they are helping other customers. That may indicate the amount of problems that are in store for you!!"}
{"Author": "Scott B", "Date": "on December 7, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works most of the time", "Text": "Works most of the time, but has a tendency to drop off line and become inaccessible."}
{"Author": "Paul C. Brown", "Date": "on December 6, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Beware! Incompatible with older Insteon devices.", "Text": "I purchased this hub to control some older Insteon devices (wired-in dimmers and plug-in dimmers) as well as newer devices. The newer devices worked flawlessly, but I struggled with the older ones - just could not make them work. Finally called support only to discover that the firmware in the older devices (e.g. LampLinc V2 2456D3) is incompatible with the new hub - and there is no upgrade path. No exchange program either. My $400 investment in the older devices is now worthless."}
{"Author": "gary bert", "Date": "on December 4, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "happy with the price"}
{"Author": "Michael", "Date": "on December 3, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Hub failed after about year.", "Text": "I know there are a lot of options for the Insteon system, but I could never get it to work well. I needed to unplug and reset the hub on a regular basis. About a year after I got it, the hub completely stooped working. I don't think it is even powering on. Now I have two Insteon wall switches, and 2 Insteon modules, and no way to control them."}
{"Author": "Clifton L. Marsh", "Date": "on December 3, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Two Stars", "Text": "Ran for a few months and then died. No lights or anything.... DEAD!"}
{"Author": "Alan L.", "Date": "on December 1, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Three Stars", "Text": "had to call them three times for three different devices. Couldn't start them."}
{"Author": "Teknoray", "Date": "on December 1, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "FIVE STARS!", "Text": "This is one of those rare things where you get MORE than what you paid for. I paid $48 for this when it was on sale and I was skeptical but I guess I got a good deal and a good product. Works perfectly and it works with Alexa! :)"}
{"Author": "Mark", "Date": "on November 30, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Failed just 2 weeks out of warranty. Common issue that is reported on their own forums.", "Text": "Worked well, until it died.. just 2 weeks past the end of the manufacturer's warranty. Reading on the insteon forums, it appears that they used a cheap, unreliable capacitor that commonly fails after 1-2 years of use. I have ordered a replacement cap, and will be replacing the old one to see if that fixes things, but a (at the time I bought it) $100 hub should last quite a bit longer than 2-weeks past the warranty."}
{"Author": "Atif A.", "Date": "on November 26, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Tried but didn't work with Cortana and Invoke", "Text": "This hub is no better than the previous 2242 model. I bought it to set it up with Cortana on Windows 10 and ultimately to Invoke through Cortana. I can see it in Cortana Connected Home and have logged in to it but still doesn't work. It acts almost identical to 2242. Money wasted. May return it since I still have the older version, which is more stable and works with all my older Insteon devices."}
{"Author": "Lynn Skaggs", "Date": "on November 26, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Firmware too far out of date to be upgraded, Hub is worthless", "Text": "The price on this item was great, but the Hub (2245-222) had a firmware that was 6 generations behind. After spending over an hour with tech support trying to determine why the Hub would not work properly they pinned it down to a firmware problem. The firmware on this unit was 1006, the latest is 1012. The problem is that the firmware can only be upgraded by the unit automatically at 2:00am PT across the internet . However firmware before 1009 can no longer be upgraded by the nightly automatic upgrade. It cannot be upgraded manually so the unit is worthless. According to tech support, this unit was manufactured many years ago and never been connected to a network to have it's firmware upgraded. I can verify that the unit I received was still sealed in its original packaging. I am returning it and have already purchased a new unit direct from SmartHome at their Black Friday sale."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on November 25, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Although I do love these it\u2019s very annoying that at least once a ...", "Text": "Although I do love these it\u2019s very annoying that at least once a week the hub won\u2019t work with Amazon echo"}
{"Author": "Nicker", "Date": "on November 24, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Meh, better products out there.", "Text": "Purchaeed this product to go along with a long string of home automation. This is by far the worst of them all. Constant hub disconnects and problems staying connect. Paired with an Echo and get the dreaded insteon hub offline far too often. For the price, look elsewhere."}
{"Author": "Beecoterie", "Date": "on November 21, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Also the app sucks. Multiple clicks just to turn this thing on", "Text": "Doesn't work by itself - you'll need to buy the hub as well. Also the app sucks. Multiple clicks just to turn this thing on. Figure out a way to have a widget or long-press menu item to access a switch."}
{"Author": "S Hazard", "Date": "on November 20, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Worked well, until it died at a very young age.", "Text": "*UPDATE*\nInsteon customer support was very helpful. They supplied me with a new replacement hub, so my system is back up and running. Hopefully the issue that I and a number of other reviewers encountered was just with that one production run. Changing my review to four stars.\n\n*ORIGINAL REVIEW*\nI purchased this system to control some of the lights in my home, and to have more solid control over lighting scenes while traveling (for home security). My Insteon hub had worked nicely for over a year, when I received an Amazon Echo last Christmas. I was pleasantly surprised to discover that the hub model I had was echo compatible, which made the setup exponentially more useful. No more fumbling to take out my phone, unlock it, and wait for an app to load just to turn the lights on or off, I could just talk to the echo to control everything. There were occasional disconnects where the Echo would report \"The Insteon hub is not responding\", but not often enough to really inconvenience me.\nJust this past week however, the hub died completely and suddenly. It won't power on, and the reset button does nothing. I'll be reaching out to Insteon support to see if they'll help, but I expect my device is well past its warranty period. I don't relish putting another $60 into this system, at that point I'll be more likely to move on to the Samsung SmartThings system. I believe that two years is entirely too short a lifespan for this type of technology, and it seems that other reviewers are reporting a dead hub at around the two year mark as well.\nIf Insteon is able to replace or repair the hub, I'll update this review to reflect the service experience."}
{"Author": "TX", "Date": "on November 19, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Three Stars", "Text": "I liked the the functionality and found it simple to setup, however the hub died after a year."}
{"Author": "Kevin Fangman", "Date": "on November 19, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "A very good way to automate your home and secure it without montly costs but you better know what your doing.", "Text": "I've got Insteon products in my primary home. It has some quirks but I like it so when I bought a vacation home I decided to put their products in there as well. That's when I discovered the issues.\n\nIn a nutshell, they do not create applications for all platforms on a equal basis. As an example they have a feature to allow for multiple homes. What they don't tell you is that it doesn't work on Android devices at all. Most features work on the Windows app and it appears all features work on IOS. I'm definitely not an Apple guy so that's a problem.\n\nIn general I found their code is a bit buggy. As an example they have light sensors that you can use to make decisions about turning things on and off. The problem is the senor works off a point of light intensity not a range. So if the light level is right at that point it rapidly switches back and fourth between on and off turning things on and off rapidly in your home.\n\nYou also need to be cautious with their support. They respond in a reasonable time frame but their answers are somewhat vague. I'm an IT professional with over 30 years experience. When I ask a technical question from a technical person I expect something more than yes or no answers. I realize I'm doing things here that are probably out of the norm but when I can come up with better ways to use their products than their technical support staff can that's an issue.\n\nThere are other minor things I could site. I still like their stuff and will continue to use it. But before you get into this you need to really think about what you want to accomplish and then how you want to do it."}
{"Author": "Quadcapable", "Date": "on November 18, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "alternatives?", "Text": "alternatives?"}
{"Author": "DuLayne Transitions", "Date": "on November 17, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Don't buy this system.", "Text": "This is the worst system. The app is deplorable. I regret ever purchasing this system. Totally unreliable and impossible to schedule let alone program the scenes or rooms. Beware!"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on November 16, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Interface with Alexa is unreliable !!!", "Text": "It works well with the Insteon app. But the integration with Alexa is unstable. I have been running three lamps with the Insteon modules for several months now. It works with Alexa most of the time. However several times a week at random intervals it refuses to accept commands from Alexa. When this happens Alexa reports \"The Insteon hub associated with this device is not responding\" and nothing happens with the lamp. Yet I am able to control the lamps from the Insteon app on my iPhone.After several hours the Insteon hub will start responding again. This is a well reported bug on the Insteon support boards but Insteon does not seem interested in fixing it.\n\nI really like the features of the Insteon product but this poor integration with Alexa has earned it a place on my DO NOT BUY list."}
{"Author": "Seaoasis", "Date": "on November 14, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Less than two weeks it quit working. Found that ...", "Text": "Less than two weeks it quit working. Found that just using other products make more sense in the long run and way less complicated. Choose wisely."}
{"Author": "JD", "Date": "on November 12, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Effective and easy to use", "Text": "Seems to be working brilliantly. Setting up the system components, including creating an Insteon account, took less time than unboxing everything -- seriously. I used the instructions, but it was so easy I could have done without them and been fine. The range doesn't seem to be a problem at all in a 2BR apartment. Dimmable LEDs work as advertised, and I have no problem with units plugged into surge protective devices. The app is easy to use and it only took about 5 minutes to customize all of the automation. I'm very happy with the turn on fade delay and dimmer set point. Meaning, when I switch the lights on, they fade from 0-75% (adjustable) over a period of 5 seconds (adjustable). It's a very pleasant effect. I've already purchased additional dimmer plugs. Great product if you understand the range and use the right bulbs etc."}
{"Author": "M. Grubert", "Date": "on November 10, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Walled garden", "Text": "This could be a great product, but unfortunately it suffers from the manufacturer keeping the protocol proprietary and closed. So the only way to get more switches is by buying them from Insteon, at whatever price they charge. As an example if you want something akin to a TV remote control that's going to cost you $45. The whole system is server-based so theoretically they could make it available for other manufacturers and hobbyists but that is not happening. I regret buying this kit and should have looked for a Z-Wave compatible one instead."}
{"Author": "Rich", "Date": "on November 9, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Four Stars", "Text": "Required for Echo."}
{"Author": "John Sholty", "Date": "on November 9, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Nightmare", "Text": "My 1st camera was a 720 and it worked for a month or so then could not be found using the Insteon app. I tried rebooting but the setup routine couldn't find the camera. Insteon Help Center told me they no longer provided support for the camera as it was a discontinued style. I begged a bit and they reluctantly agreed to troubleshoot but eventually decided the camera was faulty. I bought two new cameras which worked well for another month, then I added an outside camera. After several more weeks first one inside camera failed, then the outside camera failed then all three cameras had disappeared from access via the app. After several months of ignoring the box full of cameras in my office I attempted to reboot all cameras but the Central Hub is dead. Very frustrating as my problems may have been the Hub all along."}
{"Author": "T. Brownlow", "Date": "on November 8, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Hub works.", "Text": "The hub is easy to set up. The modules connected readily and the lights were easy to program.\nI wish the cameras worked as well. I've only used this with the included light modules. However,\nif the other accessories work as well I'll be very happy. I would recommend this product."}
{"Author": "MELINDA SANTIAGO", "Date": "on November 8, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "... 1 year 2 months I'm getting more and more disappointed with Insteon products", "Text": "Just died lasted 1 year 2 months I'm getting more and more disappointed with Insteon products."}
{"Author": "Scott Proulx", "Date": "on November 6, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "installs in minutes and works great through iphone", "Text": "this is a real value and a quality unit. installs in minutes and works great through iphone, ipad or as I also did, connected to my Amazon DOT."}
{"Author": "John Rix", "Date": "on November 4, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Do not buy this, it is not reliable!", "Text": "Works fine for a few days, then I have to power cycle it to get the thing working again, big mistake getting this Hub.\nDo not have this problem with other home automation brands, only Insteon.\nEvery few years I purchase some Insteon products to see if their reliability has improved, but it never gets better, guess they will never figure out how to make reliable products.\nThe whole point of home automation is to make things easier to control, if you spend a lot of time maintaining the system then it has no value, Insteon should have figured this out by now!"}
{"Author": "gh", "Date": "on November 2, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "So far it is working as expected."}
{"Author": "rpe", "Date": "on November 1, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Never turned on. Shouldn't leave deliveries in rain.", "Text": "Never turned on. Shouldn't leave deliveries in rain."}
{"Author": "John B.", "Date": "on November 1, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Works great"}
{"Author": "Robert Jones", "Date": "on October 31, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Doesn't play well with Alexa", "Text": "Not reliable. Frequently doesn't respond to commands through Alexa. I'm breaking up with Insteon. Got a Wink2 and I'm not looking back. Wink2 also supports many more devices!"}
{"Author": "Chris B.", "Date": "on October 30, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Works Great"}
{"Author": "dag1124", "Date": "on October 29, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Make Your Home a Smarthome", "Text": "Love this kit; makes my home a smart home. I have 3 Echo devices in my house: living room, entertainment room and bedroom. I have lights in each room with the Insteon LED Light bulbs. I can turn these lights on/off from other rooms in my house and from my app. I can turn lights on/off when away from home."}
{"Author": "rugbygame", "Date": "on October 26, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Replacing an Old Insteon Hub Can Be Time Consuming", "Text": "Once set up, the hub is rock solid and operates flawlessly. On a new installation, the setup is probably reasonable, but I was replacing an aging Insteon hub that would randomly fail to actuate controllers and switches. My replacement installation was difficult and tedious. First I had to individually remove all the devices from my account, and then set up a new account. Once my new account was set up, I had to manually add each device back into my new account and type in a new schedule for each device. Insteon does not explain the replacement procedure, and I had to search the Insteon support group for an explanation of the correct hub replacement process. One particularly annoyance was adding the two I/O sync devices for my garage door openers. I had to remove the I/O sync devices from my garage ceiling electrical outlets and connect them to the same electrical outlet that the new hub was plugged into. Once the two I/O synch devices were plugged into the same outlet as the hub, the hub was able to discover them and I could add them to my account. I probably spent 6 hours replacing the hub and reinstalling my 12 devices. I suspect the problem for the I/O synch devices was that the garage branch circuit was out of phase with the branch circuit that the hub was attached to. I caught a special 30% off sale for the hub so I was overall pleased with the replacement hub, but anyone considering replacing their old Insteon hub should be forewarned that it may be a time consuming and annoying process."}
{"Author": "D. Edwards", "Date": "on October 25, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "(No phone number on website) At times that come across as impatient and rude and I'm pretty tech savvy", "Text": "I was an Insteon customer early on. Their products are very buggy. Tech support is hard to get a hold of. (No phone number on website) At times that come across as impatient and rude and I'm pretty tech savvy.\n\nI would consider other products like Wemo. At least they have 24/7 chat support."}
