{"Author": "J. Ray", "Date": "on October 12, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I can only base my review on the compatibility with ...", "Text": "I can only base my review on the compatibility with Amazon Alexa. I have to manually go in to the app daily and discover the Insteon plugs in my home, even though they still show in my devices list, they show offline. I do not have to do this with my WeMo plugs, or any of my \"off-brand\" Alexa compatible plugs. I keep looking for an update to fix the issue, but as of now have not found one."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on October 11, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Bought to replace old one that broke!", "Text": "Have insteon products all threw my house. Bought this kit because I needed another \"hub\" seeing the one I had died after three years. After reading on the internet the hub dying after a couple of years is a common thing??? Electronics doesnt last forever folks? For $50 bucks plus two on/off modules is a great deal! My hub lasted about three years or so! Works well with amazon echo (Alexa) Only downfall is every once in a while I have to log back into my alexa app and \"refind\" all the insteon devices??? I dont know if this problem is amazons or insteons? No big deal but this happens at least once or twice a week???"}
