{"Author": "Dr.C", "Date": "on September 25, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Simple control solution for Insteon switch users", "Text": "This was fairly easy to set up with the Insteon switches around my home. Note that it only provides for fixed times for on/off or dusk/dawn on/off. It does not appear to allow arbitrary programming or interaction with most other devices. It can be remotely controlled from your smartphone using the Insteon for Hub app on the Google Playstore. I'm using it simply for dusk-to-dawn security light controls, but I'll also run Christmas lights using it during the Holiday season. Note that setting up a group of Insteon switches is much simpler than with no hub or controller since you can set up the hub and switches using the switches' Insteon addresses instead of having to run around the house manually setting them. In fact, I set each switch into the system using a test rig next to the hub to ensure that it worked before I installed the switches in their final locations."}
