{"Author": "Gary Rice", "Date": "on September 12, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works but takes a little extra effort to understand the setup instructions.", "Text": "Have only installed three leak detectors so far. Do not have any experience with any other setup so I can not make a comparison. The controller and leak sensor were fairly easy to set up but it took a few tries to get the notification set up to suit my needs. It was not quite clear to me how to set up an account and get notifications. Had to go thru it 3 times before I figured out they were tied together. If you want phone notifications,you have to set up you user name as your number@your provider. It works and has already warned us of a leak from a reverse osmosis system I installed a couple days earlier."}
{"Author": "Chris", "Date": "on September 12, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "The best product for controlling Insteon devices", "Text": "The best product for controlling Insteon devices. Allows communication with Amazon Echo or control from phone app. Simple schedule and scene set-up through the app."}
{"Author": "Scott K", "Date": "on September 11, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Absolutely this worst software I have ever used for home automation", "Text": "Absolutely this worst software I have ever used for home automation. Too many problems to list here - add something to a \"scene\" and won't remember brightness level, no adjustment for sunset or sunrise, and on and on..."}
{"Author": "Ginja Ninja", "Date": "on September 11, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Voice Control your whole house", "Text": "I love voice controlling everything in my house now. This was such a great deal on this hub, I couldn't pass it up. I already have a few light bulbs by other brands, and they work OK. But the technology behind these are so much better. Each device can be both a receiver and repeater, so I don't have any dead zones in my house that can't reach the hub. I have purchased all Insteon devices now and can control every aspect of my house by voice, motion (the motion sensor is awesome btw), phone app, or remote. I was in a wheelchair for several months after a knee surgery, and having the ability to control everything in my house from one spot was priceless. I highly recommend getting the Fan Controller Modules that go in the ceiling, the Garage Door module, and the Motion Sensor to go along with your Plug In Modules and Light Switches. Pairing this up with my Logitech Harmony Hub and I can control just about everything in my house."}
{"Author": "Katie Blankenship", "Date": "on September 9, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "One Star", "Text": "My 1st box did not work how ever I did get a neew one! Still having some trouble!"}
{"Author": "BobP", "Date": "on September 7, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Fast Set Up", "Text": "Great product\nEasy and fast setup and I can control lights from anywhere in the world."}
{"Author": "Mark Peterson", "Date": "on September 2, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Weak PC interface, no configuration backup, weak power supply.", "Text": "This is my third unit. The other two stopped working. Probably the power supply. They work well, but the Windows interface is not great. I much prefer to program it on my PC. There is no configuration backup, so when a unit fails, you have to call Smarthome to delete the account, then you have to reprogram it all over again. If you have several Insteon modules it takes quite a bit of time. The power supplies on all Insteon units are a weak design point."}
{"Author": "Cameron", "Date": "on August 31, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Biggest disappointment is you can't add or subtract time from sunrise ...", "Text": "Too simple. Can't access attributes of 6 and 8 button switches. Can't run more than one scene at a time (a house has more than one stage). Biggest disappointment is you can't add or subtract time from sunrise and sunset."}
