{"Author": "Everglades Bear", "Date": "on August 26, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Looses connection often. Not reliable.", "Text": "Looses connection often. Not reliable."}
{"Author": "SH", "Date": "on August 26, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Problems with remote detection of devices", "Text": "Purchased this kit two years ago. In general, it works well, as advertised - easy set up and easy to manage. I use it to control lights at one residence when I am away for work at a second residence for extended periods. Over past 6 months, have had repeated problems establishing a good remote connection to the hub. Open the app, devices not detected - the indicator is yellow rather than clear (off) or green (on). No matter how many times I try to connect the indicator remains yellow. Today I called the support desk. The tech person in India told me there is no way to troubleshoot the devices remotely. I have to be in the same location as the devices to troubleshoot. What good is that? It is very unsettling not to know whether my lights are functioning as I need them to when I am not home. And yet it seems that there's nothing I can do about it while I'm working remotely. Not good. This has undermined my confidence in the product. I am looking into alternates."}
